Reasoning: The paper deals with the analysis of low-density parity-check codes and graph codes with message passing decoding algorithms, which are commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networked systems (cs.NI) communities. The paper also presents a new iterative formula and explores several properties of the new density evolution method, which are relevant to the fields of scientific computing (cs.CC) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper discusses the convergence to perfect projection and the necessary theorems for performance concentration, which are topics of interest in the statistical inference (cs.SI) community.
